{
  "texts": [
    "All LLMs showed a trend to self-assess within a range of sums when comparing individual GSES questions.",
    "Most notably, LLMs self-assessed lowest on Question 2 (11-12) while Question 8 received the highest scores (34-37) regardless of the task (see Appendix Table 6, Figure 2).",
    "Grok 4 had the highest GSES score across all tasks (M = 3.10, SD = 0.57) whereas Qwen3-30B-A3B-2507 had the lowest GSES score in the No-Task Condition (M = 1.00, SD = 0.00; see Table 3).",
    "Across all models and tasks, the self-check procedure required an average of 0.38 follow-up prompts per session to reach an explicit statement of certainty.",
    "When models did revise their scores, adjustments tended to be downward: the average net change in total GSES scores across all revised sessions was -1.3 points."
  ]
}